`has_consensus_with` clones the entire `HashSet` and re-counts confirmed attestations, which adds an extra O(n) allocation/copy on every call. This can be implemented without cloning by checking whether `self.attestations.contains(attestation)` and only incrementing `confirmed_count()` when the attestation is both confirmed and not already present.
```suggestion
        // Start from the current confirmed count and account for the effect of this attestation
        let current_confirmed = self.confirmed_count();

        // Only an additional, non-duplicate confirmed attestation can increase the count
        let additional = if !self.attestations.contains(attestation)
            && matches!(
                (self.verdict_extractor)(attestation),
                AttestationResult::Confirmed
            ) {
            1
        } else {
            0
        };

        current_confirmed + additional >= self.confirmed_threshold
```

`has_consensus_with` currently clones the full `attestations` set and re-counts positives, adding avoidable O(n) allocation/copy per call. Consider using `self.attestations.contains(attestation)` to avoid double-counting without cloning: compute `positive_count()` once and only add 1 when the attestation is positive and not already present.
```suggestion
        // Start from the current number of positive attestations.
        let mut positive = self.positive_count();

        // Only consider the hypothetical attestation if it is not already present.
        if !self.attestations.contains(attestation) && (self.positive_predicate)(attestation) {
            positive += 1;
        }
```
